      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes. The candy-like taste of gummies creates a real overconsumption risk. Fat-soluble vitamins A, D, E, and K accumulate in body tissue and can cause toxicity with chronic excessive intake. Vitamin A toxicity can cause liver damage, headaches, and birth defects. Iron-containing gummies pose a poisoning risk if consumed in large quantities. Melatonin overdose can disrupt circadian rhythm. Even water-soluble vitamins like B6 can cause nerve damage at very high doses. Always store gummies out of reach of children, follow the labeled serving size, and calculate your total daily intake across all supplements to avoid exceeding Tolerable Upper Intake Levels.' },
